I did a breakdown of Marvel's Avengers, cause it's a fight-scene-heavy blockbuster action film with a moderate amount of plot. I didn't want a completely mindless action romp, nor a cerebral tale, so this split the difference perfectly.
Beautiful!!!! https://t.co/lNc9Sj4UOH

Fight 2: Black Widow needs an introduction as well, so she gets a small fight scene to show off what she can do, very similar to Loki's, but smaller scale since we just had a more major battle with more plot significance.

Fight 3: Loki needs to get Hawkeye the eye data necessary for a retinal scan which will let him get into a military base. We also need to see that the Avengers can and will fight back, so this is the first time we set up our heroes' abilities.

Fight 1: Loki appears. Introduce the villain and set up the power of the tesseract, the main focal point of the entire plot. Loki needs to show off how powerful he is here if we're going to believe him to be a threat worthy of the Avengers, so that's what this scene shows us.
@MEHNEHOYMENOY I’m super over that aspect. I was honestly glad we didn’t get the Tom Cruise Iron Man or Tobey Maguire in MOM, it was such a pandery movie already.
In Avengers there are 6 major fights, and a few of those break down further into sub-sections. Each of them is specifically motivated to continue the story in some way or another.
